      "info": {
        "contact": {
          "url": "https://api.adviceslip.com"
        },
        "description": "This API allows users to search for specific notice slips within a given database. It provides information regarding the results of search queries, indicating if there are matching slips or not.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://api.adviceslip.com"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Search Notice API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Search the Advice Slip catalogue for slips containing a given term",
        "homepage": "https://api.adviceslip.com",
        "docs_url": "https://api.adviceslip.com",
        "license_short": "Free to use; no authentication required. Operated by Tom Kiss.",
        "license_md": "- The Advice Slip JSON API is provided free of charge by Tom Kiss (© 2013–2026).\n- No API key or authentication is required.\n- Responses are cached for 2 seconds, so repeat requests within that window return the same result.\n- The creator suggests supporting the service via Ko-fi (\"buy them a coffee or beer\") if you find it useful.",
        "about_md": "This SDK is a focused subset of the [Advice Slip JSON API](https://api.adviceslip.com) run by Tom Kiss, exposing just the search endpoint. The wider API serves short pieces of advice (\"slips\") and hands out over 10 million of them each year.\n\nWhat you get from this SDK:\n\n- Full-text search via `GET /advice/search/{query}`, which returns a search object containing `total_results`, the original `query`, and an array of matching slip objects (each with `slip_id` and `advice`).\n- If no slips match the query, the API responds with a `message` object describing the notice instead of slips.\n\nOperational notes: there is no authentication, CORS is enabled, and responses are cached for 2 seconds (a repeat call inside that window returns the same result). Optional JSONP is supported via a `callback` query parameter.\n\nNote: this slug is a search-only subset of the broader `advice-slip` API and points at the same upstream service.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "search": "Full-text search over the Advice Slip catalogue at `GET /advice/search/{query}`, returning `total_results`, the submitted `query`, and an array of matching slip objects; if nothing matches, a `message` object is returned instead."
        },
